oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Rockwood, TN, 1896
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: C. F. Steinwehr, Rockwood, Tenn.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: 21st Anniversary Celebration Rockwood Lodge No. 191, I.O.O.F. [Independent Order of Odd Fellows (IOOF)], Rockwood, Tennessee, August 5, 1896. Sepia, 7.75x9.5” print on 10x12” cardboard mount. C.F. Steinwehr, Photographer, Rockwood, Tenn. View showing Johnson Building, Peterman Building, Bank Building & Arch. All on Rockwood Avenue. U.S. flags on buildings; horse drawn wagons on street. On arch: painted symbols and 'We command you to visit the sick, relieve the distressed, bury the dead and educate the orphan. Milliner sign on building at right
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Celebrations; Anniversaries; Events; Carts & wagons; Arches; Fraternal organizations; Flags;
